<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-27T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-27T08:00:00-05:00" n="295" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d295">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/2710: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-27T14:00:00+01:00">June 27,
                                1944—2 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received June 27—11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2322. Personal for the Secretary. Entirely reliable American source known to
                            Lyon<note n="43" xml:id="d295fn43">Presumably Frederick B. Lyon, Chief
                            of the Division of Foreign Activity Correlation.</note> informs me that
                        Dr. Kleist,<note n="44" xml:id="d295fn44">Peter Kleist.</note> a special
                        representative of Ribbentrop, is now in Stockholm trying to contact Allied
                        officials with peace offer and is already in touch with an old Polish friend
                        designing to use him as contact man. Informant is not certain <pb facs="0540" n="526" xml:id="pg_526"/> but believes it probable contact
                        was made by Kleist through the Pole with British last night or will be
                        today.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>